Vice President Mike Pence delivered remarks at the Floresville High School Football Stadium in Sutherland Springs, Texas, following the mass shooting at the First Baptist Church. Pence expressed condolences to the families of the victims and offered the support of the American people. He praised the bravery of law enforcement, first responders, and the community members who acted heroically during the attack. Pence emphasized the importance of faith in overcoming evil and called for unity and prayer in the face of tragedy. His wife, Karen Pence, led a prayer for comfort and peace for the affected community.